This paper deals with the problem of extracting consistent information from relational databases, which is a core topic in the field of database management (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the notion of repair, which is a common approach to dealing with inconsistent data in databases and is closely related to machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The paper provides a characterization of several complexity issues related to repairing data and computing consistent query answers, which involves algorithmic and computational aspects (cs.DS, cs.CC). Finally, the paper addresses the problem of aggregate constraints, which is a topic in artificial intelligence and optimization (cs.AI).
